						<summary>

						<p>Slab standing in Kambaḷa-gadde.</p>						

						<p>Bukka I, 1353 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This badly damaged record registers a gift of money to a deity by a <hi rend="italic">seṭṭi.</hi> All details of the gift etc. are lost. It states that <hi rend="bold">Gōparasa</hi> was governing <hi rend="bold">Bārakūru-rājya.</hi></p>						

						<p>It is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1275, Vijaya, Mārgaśira ba. 5, Monday.</hi> Barring the week-day which was Sunday, the other details correspond to <hi rend="bold">1353 A.D. December 16.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
